0billed%20as%20India's%20largest%20FDI%20proposal%20in%20mining%20and%20metallurgy%2C%20will%20create%20over%2053%2C500%20jobs%20and%20strengthen%20the%20state's%20aluminium%20value%20chain%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A99%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-irh-sign-rs-1-08-trillion-odisha-aluminium-project-mou-126070200547_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-irh-sign-rs-1-08-trillion-odisha-aluminium-project-mou-126070200547_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fadani-irh-sign-rs-1-08-trillion-odisha-aluminium-project-mou-126070200547_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Inside%20the%20strange%20side%20hustle%20of%20teaching%20AI%20to%20think%20like%20a%20lawyer%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20collage%20featuring%20a%20lawyer%20and%20AI%20prompt%20imagery%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42a36ea25092c74cca0f26%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3B%20Tyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20arbitrator%20Jessica%20Crutcher%20logs%20off%20after%20a%20day%20of%20hearing%20disputes%2C%20she%20starts%20a%20graveyard%20shift%20training%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20gets%20the%20work%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-startup-mercor-spends-more-on-tokens-than-payroll-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMercor%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20company%20that%20hires%20subject-matter%20experts%20to%20train%20artificial%20intelligence%20systems.%20She%20often%20spends%20hours%20staring%20at%20the%20walls%20of%20her%20home%20office%2C%20dreaming%20up%20legal%20problems%20that%20machines%20can't%20easily%20solve%2C%20at%20least%20not%20yet.%20One%20week%2C%20she's%20inventing%20a%20lawsuit%20over%20oil%20and%20gas%20trading%3B%20the%20next%2C%20she's%20writing%20an%20asylum%20case.%20She%20prompts%20the%20model%20and%20then%20reviews%20its%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELawyers%20have%20been%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcooley-go-lab-legora-y-combinator-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20is%20coming%20for%20some%20of%20their%20work.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Before%20that%20can%20happen%2C%20though%2C%20many%20are%20getting%20paid%20to%20teach%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECrutcher%20is%20one%20of%20a%20growing%20number%20of%20legal%20professionals%20helping%20train%20the%20very%20systems%20that%20millions%20of%20people%20increasingly%20rely%20on.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-training-account-selling-market-scam-scale-surge-mercor-facebook-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20training%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20like%20Mercor%20and%20Micro1%20have%20enlisted%20thousands%20of%20lawyers%2C%20retired%20judges%2C%20and%20paralegals%20to%20date.%20Many%20spend%20nights%20and%20weekends%20crafting%20impossible%20legal%20puzzles%2C%20grading%20chatbot%20answers%2C%20and%20showing%20frontier%20models%20how%20experienced%20lawyers%20think.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20work%20offers%20a%20front-row%20seat%20to%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20technological%20shifts%20to%20hit%20the%20profession%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20for%20many%2C%20a%20chance%20to%20help%20shape%20the%20tools%20that%20may%20one%20day%20reshape%20their%20own%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%201%20billion%20people%20now%20use%20chatbots%20like%20ChatGPT%20and%20Claude%20every%20month%20to%20draft%20emails%20and%20answer%20questions%20about%20legal%20squabbles%20from%20divorce%20to%20landlord%20disputes.%20The%20companies%20behind%20those%20systems%20want%20their%20answers%20to%20be%20as%20accurate%20as%20possible.%20To%20get%20there%2C%20they're%20paying%20lawyers%20to%20supply%20something%20the%20internet%20cannot%3A%20professional%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Crutcher%2C%20the%20work%20is%20less%20about%20the%20paycheck%20than%20staying%20close%20to%20a%20technology%20transforming%20her%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvey-ceo-winston-weinberg-200-funding-round-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epoured%20billions%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20startups%20chasing%20an%20opportunity%20to%20do%20for%20lawyers%20what%20vibe-coding%20tools%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcursor-ceo-michael-truell-spacex-elon-musk-anthropic-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECursor%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flovables-hit-400-million-arr-doubling-in-a-few-months-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELovable%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20done%20for%20programmers.%20Software%20is%20learning%20to%20review%20contracts%2C%20look%20up%20case%20law%2C%20and%20handle%20other%20routine%20work%20that%2C%20for%20decades%2C%20filled%20law%20firms'%20coffers.%20Keeping%20up%20with%20AI%2C%20Crutcher%20said%2C%20is%20part%20of%20how%20she%20%26quot%3Bremains%20relevant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20instinct%20led%20Harrison%20Margolin%20to%20start%20training%20models%20through%20Micro1.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20legal%20career%20had%20already%20put%20him%20close%20to%20Silicon%20Valley%2C%20advising%20semiconductor%20companies%20and%20software%20businesses.%20But%20the%20white-shoe%20law%20firm%20where%20he%20worked%20prohibited%20lawyers%20from%20using%20AI%20on%20client%20matters%2C%20and%20many%20colleagues%20dismissed%20the%20technology%20as%20a%20fad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMargolin%20saw%20something%20different.%20Their%20reluctance%2C%20he%20said%2C%20gave%20him%20%26quot%3Bmore%20time%20to%20get%20ahead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20spotting%20a%20recruiting%20post%20from%20Micro1%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20Margolin%20signed%20up.%20Soon%2C%20he%20was%20being%20paid%20to%20stress-test%20frontier%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20type%20of%20assignment%20is%20%26quot%3Bred%20teaming%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20creating%20legal%20scenarios%20difficult%20enough%20that%20the%20models%20would%20fail.%20His%20toughest%20challenge%20was%20a%20cross-border%20merger%20packed%20with%20conflicts.%20He%20drafted%20fake%20legal%20documents%20and%20a%20scoring%20rubric%2C%20then%20kept%20making%20the%20exercise%20harder.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicro1%20kept%20sending%20it%20back%20with%20the%20same%20note.%20The%20model%20wasn't%20sufficiently%20stumped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20exercise%20illustrates%20one%20of%20the%20biggest%20bottlenecks%20in%20legal%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20programming%2C%20models%20can%20learn%20from%20billions%20of%20lines%20of%20public%20source%20code%20and%20immediately%20verify%20whether%20code%20works.%20Legal%20reasoning%20is%20much%20harder%20to%20teach%2C%20said%20Bertie%20Vidgen%2C%20a%20researcher%20at%20Mercor.%20Much%20of%20the%20world's%20legal%20knowledge%20sits%20behind%20paywalls%20or%20inside%20confidential%20agreements.%20Even%20public%20documents%20rarely%20explain%20%3Cem%3Ewhy%3C%2Fem%3E%20lawyers%20made%20particular%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20human%20experts%20come%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20recently%2C%20Margolin%20has%20shifted%20to%20writing%20%26quot%3Bgolden%20responses%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20ideal%20answers%20that%20models%20can%20learn%20from%20rather%20than%20trying%20to%20trick%20them%20into%20failing.%20Isabel%20Yishu%20Yang%2C%20a%20special%20projects%20lead%20at%20Micro1%2C%20describes%20the%20work%20as%20%26quot%3Bturning%20lawyers%20into%20law%20professors.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pay%20is%20respectable%2C%20though%20hardly%20Big%20Law%20money.%20Mercor%20advertises%20rates%20between%20%24100%20and%20%24200%20an%20hour%20for%20legal%20experts.%20Micro1%20says%20compensation%20ranges%20based%20on%20different%20levels%20of%20seniority%20and%20role%20type.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawyers%20Business%20Insider%20spoke%20with%20all%20said%20the%20money%20was%20secondary%20to%20understanding%20where%20the%20profession%20is%20heading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEntertainment%20lawyer%20Charley%20Kelsey%20reached%20the%20same%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20at%20Lionsgate%2C%20he%20wasn't%20allowed%20to%20use%20AI%20because%20clients%20prohibited%20it.%20Rather%20than%20wait%20for%20the%20legal%20industry%20to%20embrace%20the%20technology%2C%20he%20left%20to%20start%20his%20own%20practice%20and%20began%20taking%20projects%20through%20Micro1.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20recent%20assignment%20involved%20creating%20an%20imaginary%20video%20game%2C%20complete%20with%20screenshots%2C%20logos%2C%20licensing%20agreements%2C%20and%20posters%2C%20then%20asking%20the%20model%20to%20untangle%20the%20copyright%20and%20trademark%20issues%20he%20slipped%20into%20the%20materials.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20work%20unexpectedly%20changed%20how%20he%20practiced%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKelsey%20said%20lawyers%20often%20jump%20from%20a%20client's%20question%20to%20an%20answer%20built%20on%20instinct%20and%20experience.%20Training%20AI%2C%20he%20said%2C%20forced%20him%20to%20slow%20down%20and%20examine%20every%20step%20of%20that%20reasoning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20recalled%20one%20client%20asking%20whether%20a%20taxidermied%20bear%20could%20be%20copyrighted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20instinct%20was%20no.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20after%20working%20through%20the%20analysis%20the%20same%20way%20he%20teaches%20models%20to%20do%2C%20he%20discovered%20case%20law%20treating%20taxidermy%20as%20sculpture%20%E2%80%94%20and%20therefore%20potentially%20eligible%20for%20copyright%20protection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20the%20side%20gig%20stopped%20being%20a%20side%20gig.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20Kelsey%20gave%20up%20practicing%20law%20full%20time%20and%20joined%20Micro1.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20doesn't%20believe%20he's%20automating%20lawyers%20out%20of%20existence.%20AI%20may%20draft%20contracts%20faster%20or%20summarize%20legal%20research%2C%20but%20it%20still%20can't%20reassure%20anxious%20clients%2C%20read%20the%20room%20during%20settlement%20negotiations%2C%20or%20argue%20before%20a%20judge.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20artificial%20intelligence%20will%20squeeze%2C%20he%20argues%2C%20is%20the%20work%20that%20didn't%20require%20much%20judgment%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawyers-moonlighting-ai-training-mercor-micro1-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782982801000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a42a36ea25092c74cca0f26%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flawyers-moonlighting-ai-training-mercor-micro1-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22AI%20has%20created%20a%20booming%20new%20side%20hustle%20for%20lawyers%3A%20training%20the%20systems%20that%20could%20one%20day%20take%20over%20their%20work.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22mrussell%40businessinsider.com%20(Melia%20Russell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2260-year-old%20man%20dies%20after%20falling%20into%20uncovered%20manhole%20in%20Mumbai%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782982735000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-132135992%2Cimgsize-70938.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fmumbai%2Fmumbai-man-missing-after-falling-into-open-stormwater-drain-during-civic-repair-work%2Farticleshow%2F132133862.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%2060-year-old%20man%2C%20Aslam%20Isak%20Shaikh%2C%20has%20vanished%20after%20plunging%20into%20an%20open%20stormwater%20drain%20on%20Khairani%20Road%20in%20Mumbai's%20Sakinaka%20area.%20The%20incident%20occurred%20while%20c