figure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20years%20for%20Aimee%20Young%20to%20realize%20she'd%20been%20doing%20a%20job%20nobody%20had%20asked%20her%20to%20do.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%202020%2C%20the%20human%20resources%20executive%20returned%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbig-companies-maternity-parental-leave-policies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ematernity%20leave%3C%2Fa%3E%20just%20as%20the%20world%20was%20descending%20into%20a%20global%20pandemic.%20She%20expected%20to%20devote%20most%20of%20her%20emotional%20energy%20to%20her%20infant%20daughter.%20Instead%2C%20much%20of%20it%20went%20to%20the%20adults%20she%20managed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYoung%2C%20who's%20now%2039%20and%20based%20in%20London%2C%20was%20the%20most%20senior%20woman%20on%20her%20team.%20As%20COVID-19%20upended%20the%20workplace%2C%20colleagues%20sought%20her%20out%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-emotional-labor-really-is-and-why-it-matters-2026-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edebrief%20difficult%20conversations%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20process%20their%20anxieties%2C%20and%20navigate%20squabbles%20between%20them.%20They%20brought%20her%20their%20fears%2C%20frustrations%2C%20and%20uncertainties%20%E2%80%94%20stemming%20both%20from%20home%20and%20from%20work.%20Almost%20by%20default%2C%20Young%20started%20an%20unofficial%20second%20job%20as%20in-house%20therapist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOn%20the%20surface%2C%20it%20looked%20like%20I%20was%20thriving%20because%20I%20was%20connected%2C%20respected%2C%20and%20trusted%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BBut%20behind%20the%20scenes%2C%20nobody%20was%20asking%20if%20I%20was%20OK.%26quot%3B%20With%20hindsight%2C%20she%20says%2C%20she%20recognized%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwomen-workplace-emotional-labor-dei-mckinsey-leanin-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eemotional%20labor%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20had%20taken%20on%20was%20%26quot%3Bthe%20perfect%20recipe%20for%20burnout.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20dozen%20managers%20I%20spoke%20to%20for%20this%20article%2C%20many%20described%20strikingly%20similar%20experiences%20of%20tending%20to%20their%20colleagues'%20uneasy%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Epsyches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKate%2C%20a%2041-year-old%20based%20in%20Boston%2C%20tells%20me%20she%20quit%20her%20job%20in%20consulting%20in%20part%20because%20the%20%26quot%3Btherapy%26quot%3B%20she%20says%20she%20felt%20like%20she%20was%20expected%20to%20provide%20the%20people%20she%20managed%20was%20%26quot%3Buntenable.%26quot%3B%20A%2042-year-old%20manager%20who%20works%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-soaring-healthcare-costs-are-changing-where-millionaires-move-2025-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehealthcare%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20put%20it%20bluntly%3A%20%26quot%3BMy%20actual%20job%20that%20I'm%20paid%20for%20doesn't%20keep%20me%20up%20at%20night.%20But%20this%20work%20of%20making%20sure%20the%20people%20who%20work%20for%20me%20feel%20happy%20and%20seen%20in%20a%20super%20stressful%20world%20absolutely%20does.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20empathy%20moved%20from%20the%20margins%20of%20management%20theory%20to%20the%20center%20of%20leadership%20practice.%20CEOs%20from%20Marriott's%20Arne%20Sorenson%20to%20Bumble's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeet-bumble-ceo-whitney-wolfe-herd-net-worth-family-ipo-2020-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWhitney%20Wolfe%20Herd%3C%2Fa%3E%20publicly%20emphasized%20staff%20well-being%20and%20recognizing%20employees'%20whole%20selves%2C%20marking%20a%20sharp%20departure%20from%20the%20hard-charging%2C%20Miltonian%20shareholder-maximizing%20managerial%20style%20that%20had%20dominated%20the%20previous%20half-century.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESix%20years%20later%2C%20that%20expectation%20hasn't%20disappeared.%20If%20anything%2C%20layoffs%2C%20AI%20disruption%2C%20economic%20uncertainty%2C%20and%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworkplace-loyalty-corporate-america-dysfunction-employers-employees-att-jobs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eerosion%20of%20workplace%20loyalty%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20left%20employees%20looking%20to%20their%20managers%20for%20even%20more%20emotional%20support.%20The%20effect%20has%20been%20a%20blurring%20of%20lines%20between%20managerial%20responsibilities%20and%20the%20more%20therapeutic%2C%20ill-defined%20work%20that%20people%20like%20Young%20found%20themselves%20inundated%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearchers%20have%20begun%20calling%20the%20latter%20the%20%26quot%3Bempathy%20tax%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20the%20largely%20invisible%20work%20of%20supporting%20colleagues%2C%20absorbing%20anxiety%2C%20and%20tending%20to%20workplace%20well-being%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20work%20that%20falls%20disproportionately%20on%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20much%20of%20corporate%20America%20has%20shifted%20in%20the%20opposite%20direction%3A%20celebrating%20a%20harder-edged%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmeta-ruthless-management-style-reckoning-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etake-no-prisoners%20vision%20of%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20especially%20prominent%20in%20Silicon%20Valley%20that%20prizes%20decisiveness%2C%20competitiveness%2C%20and%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerica-girl-boss-women-musk-zuckerberg-dimon-alpha-male-backlash-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emasculine%20energy%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20divergence%20is%20increasingly%20hard%20to%20ignore.%20Psychologists%2C%20managerial%20researchers%2C%20and%20the%20managers%20caught%20in%20the%20middle%20%E2%80%94%20between%20colleagues'%20emotional%20needs%20and%20the%20boss'%20mantras%20to%20effectively%20ignore%20them%20%E2%80%94%20say%20that%20this%20gap%20threatens%20to%20exacerbate%20burnout%20and%20existing%20inequalities%20in%20the%20economy.%20They%20also%20say%20that%20the%20fix%20starts%20with%20companies%20acknowledging%20the%20true%20cost%20of%20this%20often%20invisible%20load%20and%20their%20responsibility%20to%20alleviate%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EA%20growing%20body%20of%20social%20psychology%20research%20helps%20explain%20why%20women%20pay%20a%20steeper%20empathy%20tax%20than%20men.%20Many%20studies%20show%20that%2C%20thanks%20to%20deeply%20ingrained%20gender%20norms%2C%20women%20are%20expected%20to%20demonstrate%20warmth%20and%20caring%20in%20the%20workplace%20and%20are%20judged%20negatively%20when%20they%20don't.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBobbi%20Thomason%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20applied%20behavioral%20science%20at%20Pepperdine%20Graziadio%20Business%20School%20who%20studies%20gender%20and%20leadership%2C%20says%20those%20expectations%20reflect%20what%20researchers%20describe%20as%20%26quot%3Bbenevolent%20sexism.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BWomen%20are%20wonderful%2C%20they're%20so%20nice%2C%20they're%20so%20caring%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BThese%20things%20all%20sound%20perfectly%20good%20until%20you%20realize%20that%20using%20all%20your%20time%20and%20energy%20being%20kind%20and%20giving%20to%20everyone%20else%20is%20taking%20away%20from%20time%20and%20energy%20you%20could%20spend%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdone-being-girlboss-choosing-motherhood-over-money-and-career-growth-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoving%20your%20own%20career%20forward%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWomen%20are%20conditioned%20to%20believe%20this%20is%20simply%20their%20role%20to%20play%20%E2%80%94%20often%20without%20ever%20questioning%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Gabriele%20Geist%2C%20a%2047-year-old%20who%20left%20investment%20banking%20in%202016%20and%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-coach-recommends-four-hour-burnout-proof-job-application-routine-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eadvises%20organizations%20on%20burnout%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20nervous%20system%20regulation%2C%20and%20the%20retention%20of%20senior%20women.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMartha%20Fernandez%2C%20a%20clinical%20social%20worker%2C%20says%20that%20this%20conditioning%20can%20quickly%20turn%20into%20a%20self-perpetuating%20cycle.%20The%20people%20doing%20the%20most%20emotional%20labor%20%26quot%3Bare%20usually%20the%20last%20to%20complain%2C%20because%20complaining%20about%20caring%20feels%20like%20admitting%20you're%20not%20actually%20caring%2C%20which%20is%20its%20own%20trap%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20November%20and%20December%20last%20year%2C%20researchers%20at%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsloanreview.mit.edu%2Farticle%2Fthe-empathy-tax-female-leaders-pay%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epolled%20more%20than%20350%20professional%20women%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20managerial%20roles%2C%20and%20found%20that%20more%20than%2080%25%20said%20they%20spend%20at%20least%2030%25%20of%20their%20workweek%20on%20caring%20tasks%3A%20listening%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-coding-tools-software-engineers-workplace-paralysis-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecolleagues'%20anxieties%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20offering%20encouragement%2C%20or%20monitoring%20how%20people%20around%20them%20are%20feeling.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20they're%20spending%20more%20than%20a%20day%20of%20work%20as%20quasi-therapists%20every%20workweek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20line%20that%20kept%20coming%20up%20when%20we%20were%20doing%20this%20research%20was%20that%20women%20are%20becoming%20the%20emotional%20infrastructure%20of%20modern%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Deepa%20Purushothaman%2C%20an%20executive%20fellow%20at%20HBS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20strain%20that%20comes%20with%20that%20is%20growing.%20When%20the%20researchers%20asked%20the%20women%20how%20their%20time%20spent%20on%20caring%20tasks%20had%20changed%20compared%20to%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20some%2059%25%20reported%20an%20increase%20in%20emotional%20labor%20at%20work.%20That's%20not%20surprising%2C%20as%20workers%20in%202026%20bring%20into%20the%20office%20existential%20worries%20about%20the%20economy%2C%20job%20security%2C%20healthcare%2C%20the%20state%20of%20democracy%2C%20climate%20change%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-workplace-more-productive-less-social-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20disruption%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20anxiety%20stemming%20from%20all%20of%20this%2C%20and%20the%20resulting%20empathy%20tax%20felt%20by%20many%2C%20may%20also%20be%20reshaping%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flayoffs-job-market-unemployed-americans-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elabor%20market%3C%2Fa%3E%20itself.%20More%20than%20455%2C000%20women%20left%20the%20US%20workforce%20between%20January%20and%20August%20of%202025%2C%20and%20a%20survey%20of%20more%20than%201%2C000%20women%20conducted%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year%20by%20Catalyst%2C%20a%20workforce%20consultancy%2C%20found%20that%20many%20quit%20because%20the%20combined%20weight%20of%20paid%20work%2C%20still-disproportionate%20caregiving%2C%20and%20invisible%20emotional%20labor%20had%20become%20harder%20to%20sustain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMen%20pay%20empathy%20taxes%2C%20too.%20But%20Purushothaman%20says%20that%20in%20the%20conversations%20she's%20engaged%20in%20for%20her%20research%2C%20men%20did%20not%20describe%20feeling%20the%20same%20pressure%20to%20provide%20emotional%20support%20as%20women%2C%20and%20in%20many%20cases%20they%20didn't%20observe%20this%20work%20happening%20around%20them.%20%26quot%3BWe%20aren't%20saying%20men%20don't%20do%20this%20work%20at%20all%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Colleen%20Ammerman%2C%20director%20of%20HBS's%20Race%2C%20Gender%20%26amp%3B%20Equity%20Initiative%2C%20who%20led%20the%20study%20with%20Purushothaman.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20just%20saying%20that%20women%20experience%20substantially%20greater%20expectations%20to%20do%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20things%20that%20has%20made%20the%20emotional%20labor%20many%20managers%20describe%20particularly%20frustrating%20is%20that%20it%20has%20unfolded%20alongside%20the%20growing%20popularity%20of%20a%20leadership%20culture%20that%20espouses%20very%20different%20traits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%2C%20who%20attended%20last%20month's%20UFC%20cage%20match%20on%20the%20White%20House%20South%20Lawn%2C%20has%20lamented%20what%20he%20described%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmark-zuckerberg-masculine-energy-meta-facebook-feminine-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20lack%20of%20%26quot%3Bmasculine%20energy%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20corporate%20culture%2C%20arguing%20that%20businesses%20benefit%20from%20more%20aggression%20and%20competitiveness.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatt-ceo-memo-workplace-loyalty-dead-employees-job-security-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAT%26amp%3BT%20CEO%20John%20Stankey%3C%2Fa%3E%20sent%20a%20memo%20to%20managers%20last%20year%20noting%20that%20the%20company%20has%20%26quot%3Bconsciously%20shifted%20away%26quot%3B%20from%20%26quot%3Ban%20'employment%20deal'%20rooted%20in%20loyalty.%26quot%3B%20A%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20executive%20told%20employees%20he%20wanted%20%26quot%3Bmore%20hustle%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-women-ceo-succession-race-dimon-rohrbaugh-petno-lake-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EJamie%20Dimon%2C%20the%20bank's%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20criticizing%20staff%20for%20pushing%20back%20against%20a%20five-day%20return-to-office%20policy.%20Venture%20capitalist%20Marc%20Andreessen%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20has%20become%20a%20leading%20voice%20for%20a%20strain%20of%20founder%20culture%20that%20prizes%20intensity%2C%20resilience%2C%20and%20execution.%20He%20recently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmarc-andreessen-zero-introspection-debate-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edismissed%20introspection%20and%20self-reflection%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20distraction%2C%20and%20argued%20that%20workers%20should%20instead%20%26quot%3Bretardmaxx.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20message%20is%20often%20implicit%20rather%20than%20explicit%2C%20but%20it%20is%20nevertheless%20powerful%3A%20Some%20of%20the%20richest%2C%20most%20visible%2C%20and%20most%20powerful%20executives%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmistake-helped-ceo-learn-leadership-lesson-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eglorifying%20a%20type%20of%20leadership%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20values%20toughness%20and%20not%20empathy%2C%20and%20this%20creates%20environments%20in%20which%20employees%20feel%20more%20limited%20in%20terms%20of%20whom%20they%20can%20confide%20in%20when%20things%20get%20tough.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAimee%20Young%20says%20that%20her%20inbox%20is%20full%20of%20messages%20from%20midlevel%20and%20senior%20women%20who%20are%20experiencing%20exactly%20this%20right%20now.%20%26quot%3BThey're%20doing%20more%20emotional%20labor%20in%20a%20culture%20that%20respects%20it%20less%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20they're%20burning%20out%20faster%20as%20a%20result.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20what's%20to%20be%20done%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECaroline%20Stokes%2C%20a%20leadership%20strategist%20and%20executive%20coach%2C%20says%20that%20the%20first%20thing%20we%20need%20to%20do%20is%20acknowledge%20that%20framing%20the%20issue%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bempathy%20tax%26quot%3B%20might%20actually%20be%20harmful.%20%26quot%3BIt%20hands%20men%20an%20opt-out%20and%20lets%20organizations%20commodify%20the%20issue%20without%20fixing%20the%20culture%20that%20created%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20adds.%20%26quot%3BIt%20pathologizes%20women%20absorbing%20anxiety%20instead%20of%20addressing%20the%20systemic%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20onus%2C%20says%20Stokes%2C%20has%20to%20be%20on%20CEOs%20in%20setting%20clear%20boundaries%20on%20what%20employees%20should%20and%20shouldn't%20bring%20to%20their%20managers.%20Executives%20should%20tell%20their%20employees%20directly%20that%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbrene-brown-interview-silicon-valley-bad-bosses-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evulnerability%20at%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20dumping%20on%20your%20bosses%20and%20line%20managers%20or%20colleagues%20and%20expecting%20them%20to%20hold%20space%20for%20you.%26quot%3B%20It's%20%26quot%3Babout%20being%20able%20to%20say%20'I%20don't%20know%2C'%20or%20'I%20need%20help%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20adds%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20not%20'let%20me%20process%20my%20bad%20weekend%20trauma%20with%20you.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrenda%20Fahn%2C%20a%20marriage%20and%20family%20therapist%2C%20says%20she%20has%20seen%20the%20emotional%20stress%20that's%20heaped%20on%20women%20in%20the%20workplace%20lead%20to%20depression%2C%20anxiety%2C%20sleep%20issues%2C%20resentment%2C%20and%20a%20loss%20of%20interest%20in%20intimacy.%20It's%20important%2C%20she%20says%2C%20to%20understand%20that%20empathy%20can%20be%20%26quot%3Blearned.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20skill%2C%20and%20the%20more%20companies%20recognize%20its%20value%20and%20the%20tangible%20benefits%20it%20brings%20to%20outcomes%20and%20productivity%2C%20the%20better%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELauren%20Smith%20Brody%2C%20founder%20and%20CEO%20of%20women's%20workforce%20consultancy%20The%20Fifth%20Trimester%2C%20urges%20her%20coaching%20clients%20to%20keep%20a%20written%20record%20of%20all%20of%20the%20emotional%20work%20they%20do.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20meticulously%20keep%20track%2C%20suddenly%20you%20can%20see%20a%20pattern%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20%26quot%3BIt%20becomes%20tangible%2C%20something%20you%20can%20describe%20as%20a%20real%20professional%20skill%20during%20your%20performance%20review.%20And%20once%20you%20can%20quantify%20it%2C%20it%20becomes%20easier%20for%20organizations%20to%20value%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20impossible%20to%20put%20a%20precise%20figure%20on%20the%20value%20of%20empathy%2C%20studies%20have%20unequivocally%20linked%20empathetic%20leadership%20to%20higher%20employee%20engagement%2C%20stronger%20organizational%20commitment%2C%20greater%20innovation%2C%20and%20better%20job%20performance.%20One%20EY%20study%20from%202021%20found%20that%2087%25%20of%20workers%20said%20they%20felt%20that%20mutual%20empathy%20between%20them%20and%20their%20leaders%20increased%20their%20efficiency%2C%20while%2086%25%20said%20they%20believed%20it%20enhances%20innovation%2C%20and%2081%25%20said%20they%20thought%20it%20increased%20company%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomason%20cautions%20against%20assuming%20the%20answer%20is%20simply%20for%20women%20to%20establish%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboundaries-work-resentment-audit-productivity-executive-coach-melody-wilding-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efirmer%20boundaries%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20order%20for%20this%20important%20empathy%20work%20to%20be%20shared.%20Research%20consistently%20shows%20that%20women%20are%20judged%20differently%20than%20men%20when%20they%20prioritize%20their%20own%20needs%2C%20she%20says.%20What%20can%20look%20like%20an%20inability%20to%20say%20no%20is%20often%20a%20rational%20calculation%20about%20how%20that%20refusal%20will%20be%20received.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20that%20you%20don't%20know%20how%20to%20have%20a%20boundary%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%20Women%20are%20often%20weighing%20the%20professional%20cost%20of%20setting%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmpathy%20and%20emotional%20work%20often%20happen%20spontaneously%20and%20in%20an%20unstructured%20way%20%E2%80%94%20even%20behind%20closed%20doors%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20doesn't%20make%20it%20any%20less%20important%20than%20the%20structured%2C%20predictable%2C%20and%20easily%20measurable%20work%20that%20managers%20do.%20It%20has%20to%20be%20recognized%2C%20acknowledged%2C%20measured%2C%20and%20rewarded%2C%20says%20Ammerman.%20%26quot%3BThe%20solution%20isn't%20to%20tell%20people%20to%20stop%20doing%20this%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Smith%20Brody.%20%26quot%3BBoundaries%20matter%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20organizations%20have%20to%20reward%20this%20kind%20of%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20adds.%20%26quot%3BBecause%2C%20as%20we%20know%2C%20there%20is%20a%20real%20business%20return%20on%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjosie-cox%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_self%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3EJosie%20Cox%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3Eis%20a%20journalist%20who%20has%20worked%20for%20publications%20like%20Reuters%2C%20The%20Independent%2C%20and%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal.%20She%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%2C%20%26quot%3BWomen%20Money%20Power%3A%20The%20Rise%20and%20Fall%20of%20Economic%20Equality.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-cost-empathy-tax-work-women-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782979981000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a457cb91aaffe3020cb1e56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhidden-cost-empathy-tax-work-women-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22White-collar%20women%20spend%20almost%20two%20days%20a%20week%20as%20their%20coworkers'%20therapist%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Josie%20Cox)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BHave%20A%20Funny%20Personality%26quot%3B%3A%20Dentist%20Who%20Mocked%20Ketan%2