ution%20he%20knows%20quite%20well%3A%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffather-of-internet-vint-cerf-on-ai-chatbots-chatgpt-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EVinton%20Cerf%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20now%2083-year-old%20who%20helped%20invent%20the%20networking%20protocols%20that%20underpin%20the%20modern%20web%2C%20has%20important%20guidance%20for%20the%20AI%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20a%20panel%20this%20week%20with%20computer%20scientists%20and%20Databricks%20cofounder%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-researcher-ai-models-analyze-millions-of-words-at-once-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMatei%20Zaharia%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0at%20the%20Open%20Frontiers%20conference%2C%20Cerf%20highlighted%20several%20principles%20that%20could%20help%20determine%20whether%20AI%20reaches%20its%20full%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22335beb44-748e-4ebd-90e6-53807c002555%5C%22%3EOpen%20standards%20matter%20more%20than%20closed%20systems%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECerf%20said%20the%20internet%20only%20became%20ubiquitous%20because%20no%20single%20company%20owned%20it%2C%20and%20everyone%20could%20use%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20case%20of%20internet%2C%20it%20only%20worked%20because%20it%20was%20going%20to%20be%20distributed%20to%20begin%20with%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cerf.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20we%20left%20the%20rules%20very%20open.%20We%20just%20said%20if%20you%20can%20find%20somebody%20to%20connect%20to%20and%20you%20follow%20the%20rules%20of%20the%20protocols%2C%20it%20should%20work.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20common%20protocols%20meant%20that%20a%20university%20network%20in%20California%2C%20a%20government%20research%20lab%2C%20and%20a%20commercial%20internet%20service%20provider%20could%20all%20connect%20using%20the%20same%20technical%20language.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECerf%20said%20AI%20is%20approaching%20the%20same%20inflection%20point%20at%20which%20the%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbotsitting-frustrating-ai-strategist-hires-humans-instead-2026-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20agents%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20demand%20%26quot%3Binteroperability%20and%20standardization.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22880df005-b1bd-4cf0-9d6d-5ac7a2ca0da5%5C%22%3EAI%20agents%20will%20need%20better%20ways%20to%20communicate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20we%20might%20speak%20to%20an%20AI%20agent%20in%20our%20native%20tongues%2C%20those%20vernaculars%20won't%20be%20ideal%20for%20our%20agents%20to%20work%20together%20effectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECerf%20said%20natural%20language%20may%20not%20be%20enough%20for%20agents%20to%20work%20together%20reliably%20or%20to%20create%20interfaces%20that%20enable%20developers%20to%20innovate%20without%20disrupting%20the%20entire%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20English%20is%20going%20to%20be%20the%20best%20choice%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Cerf.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20ambiguity%2C%20and%20I%20think%20precision%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-agents-internet-dark-google-openai-anthropic-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Einter-agent%20interaction%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20going%20to%20be%20very%2C%20very%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHuman%20languages%20often%20rely%20on%20context%2C%20inference%2C%20and%20multiple%20meanings%20for%20the%20same%20words.%20Cerf%20said%20AI%20agents%20will%20need%20communication%20methods%20that%20minimize%20vagueness%20so%20each%20system%20can%20reliably%20interpret%20requests%20and%20commitments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAn%20agent%20really%20needs%20to%20be%20sure%20the%20other%20agent%20understands%20what%20it%20is%20that%20they%20just%20agreed%20to%20do%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Cerf%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d71f22e-70a5-475d-bc4f-063a74377803%5C%22%3EThe%20biggest%20technologies%20become%20platforms%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20internet%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ECerf%20said%2C%20transformative%20technologies%20aren't%20stand-alone%20products%20but%20must%20become%20foundations%20that%20enable%20others%20to%20build.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20lot%20of%20the%20successes%20come%20from%20enabling%20technologies%2C%20whether%20it's%20a%20platform%20or%20some%20other%20fundamental%20element%20that%20others%20can%20build%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Cerf%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%2C%20Amazon%2C%20Netflix%2C%20and%20millions%20of%20smaller%20developers%20built%20services%20on%20top%20of%20the%20same%20underlying%20internet%20infrastructure.%20Cerf%20said%20the%20same%20principle%20applies%20to%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20if%20you%20really%20wanted%20to%20look%20for%20impact%2C%20think%20about%20things%20that%20enable%20other%20people%20to%20do%20things%20that%20they%20want%20to%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Cerf%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvinton-cerf-artificial-intelligence-lessons-from-early-internet-2026-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782964921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6a45a1191aaffe3020cb1f12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvinton-cerf-artificial-intelligence-lessons-from-early-internet-2026-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22From%20standardization%20to%20turning%20a%20product%20into%20a%20platform%2C%20Vinton%20Cerf%20said%20there%20are%20lessons%20AI%20must%20learn%20from%20the%20internet%20boom.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22katherineli%40insider.com%20(Katherine%20Li)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Cuba%20faces%20an%20unceasing%20crisis%20-%20but%20its%20people%20are%20refusing%20to%20give%20up%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1782964740000%2C%22vis